VI. 1 It is to be remarked that it sometimes happens that sup- pli-ants are defended [provisorily], till their case can be fairly judged. So Demophon says to the messenger of Eurystheus, that if he has any charge against the refugees, he will obtain justice, but that till then, they will not be given up.
